11 Change Logs
**************

PHP mode can help generate `ChangeLog' files, a widely-adopted format
for documenting the changes made to source code-especially software.
PHP mode and Emacs will determine the current function, file name,
author information and date and use it all to prepare a properly
formatted `ChangeLog' entry in the file.

   The `add-change-log-entry' commands can be run from within a buffer
containing a PHP buffer, or from a buffer in Diff mode with a revision
patch to a PHP source file.  *Note Diff Mode: (emacs)Diff Mode.

`C-x 4 a'
     Add an entry in a `ChangeLog' file opened in another window, or
     add a new line to the already begun entry
     (`add-change-log-entry-other-window').  Provides the file name and
     the respective function name, when applicable, for the current
     point.  The point can be in a PHP source file, or in the hunk of a
     diff file.(1)  This command will also add the current author and
     date to the entry.


   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1) *Note Diff Mode: (emacs)Diff Mode.


